    <option 
		ID="Option_LargerFolk_DynamicWeightGainOn"
	    DisplayText="Dynamic Weight Gain ({{R|new save}})"
	    Category="Mods: Larger Folk"
	    Type="Checkbox" 
			Default="No"
	>
		<helptext>
			Turn this on if you wanna try it out. If disabled, the fat sprites are used no matter what, and weight-based effects like stuckage and chair-breaking will not occur.

			The default is {{w|Disabled}}.
		</helptext>
	</option>
	
	<option 
		ID="Option_LargerFolk_WeightNames"
		Requires="Option_LargerFolk_DynamicWeightGainOn==Yes"
	    DisplayText="Display Weight in Names ({{R|new save}})"
	    Category="Mods: Larger Folk"
	    Type="Checkbox" 
			Default="Yes"
	>
		<helptext>
			This option displays a creatures current weight stage as an adjective in their display name. I feel like it's a bit much to have it display all the time, so I've added a toggle if you don't want this to happen.

			The default is {{w|Disabled}}.
		</helptext>
	</option>
	
	<option 
		ID="Option_LargerFolk_ArmorEffects"
	    DisplayText="Armor-Based Weight Effects (DOESN'T WORK WELL, WORK IN PROGRESS). ({{R|new save}})"
	    Category="Mods: Larger Folk"
	    Type="Checkbox" 
			Default="No"
	>
		<helptext>
			Turn it on if you reaaally want to try it out, but it's very basic and buggy.

			The default is {{w|Disabled}}.
		</helptext>
	</option>
